		section.intro
			.container
				.animation-container.vertical.left.top.extra-height#trigger
					.animated
				p.large Ever wanted to build the next Snapchat? Program a drone? Build a website that connects people across the globe? Come to HackTJ and work with your friends to build something cool, learn new tricks, and have a fantastic time!

		section.red.faq
			.container
				.animation-container.vertical.left.top
					.animated.white
				.header-row
					.animation-container.horizontal.left-side
						.animated.left.white
					h1.section-title FAQ
					.animation-container.horizontal.right-side
						.animated.left.white
				ul.faq-container
					//- General Questions
					.row
						li.question-group
							h3.question What is HackTJ?
								.icon.icon-plus
								.icon.icon-close
							.answer: p HackTJ is a student-run hackathon at TJHSST, where you will have 24 hours to learn how to code and/or work with your friends to make your idea come to life.
						li.question-group
							h3.question When is HackTJ?
								.icon.icon-plus
								.icon.icon-close
							.answer: p HackTJ will start on Saturday, February 6 and run until Sunday, February 7. If you need to arrive late or leave early, please <a href="mailto:hello@hacktj.org">let us know</a> ahead of time.
						li.question-group
							h3.question Who can attend?
								.icon.icon-plus
								.icon.icon-close
							.answer: p HackTJ is open to any and all current high school students. If you're not a high school student but would like to attend, consider coming <a href="" onclick="return false;">as a mentor</a>.
					//- Registration Questions
					.row
						li.question-group
							h3.question Is there any cost?
								.icon.icon-plus
								.icon.icon-close
							.answer: p Nope! HackTJ is completely free!
						li.question-group
							h3.question Is there a deadline?
								.icon.icon-plus
								.icon.icon-close
							.answer: p Yes. Registration will be closed on Feburary 1st, but don't worry about that â€“ go ahead and register now!
						li.question-group
							h3.question.small Do you have a code of conduct?
								.icon.icon-plus
								.icon.icon-close
							.answer: p Yes, good question! We have adopted the <a href="http://static.mlh.io/docs/mlh-code-of-conduct.pdf" target="_blank">MLH code of conduct</a>, which all attendees will be required to adhere to. 
					//- Hacking Questions
					.row
						li.question-group
							h3.question Isn't hacking illegal?
								.icon.icon-plus
								.icon.icon-close
							.answer: p In the context of a hackathon, "hacking" is to build a real application over the length of the event. It's important to not confuse this with illegal hacking, which is gaining unauthorized access to a computer. 
						li.question-group
							h3.question Do I need a team?
								.icon.icon-plus
								.icon.icon-close
							.answer: p If you already have a team of 2-4 people you want to work with, that's awesome! If not don't worry because we'll have an opportunity for people to join a team if they need one.
						li.question-group
							h3.question.small What if I don't know how to code?
								.icon.icon-plus
								.icon.icon-close
							.answer: p Come to HackTJ! Coding is fun, creative, and an important skill, and HackTJ is the perfect way to learn. We'll have workshops and mentors to help guide you. 
					//- Food and supplies questions
					.row
						li.question-group
							h3.question What should I bring?
								.icon.icon-plus
								.icon.icon-close
							.answer: p You'll need to bring your laptop, phone, chargers, a sleeping bag/pillow, toiletries, and extra clothing. We suggest you bring a set of nice clothes for demos; you'll want to make the best impression.
						li.question-group
							h3.question Will there be food?
								.icon.icon-plus
								.icon.icon-close
							.answer: p Yes. Lots and lots of food.
						li.question-group
							h3.question.small.not-mobile What if I have dietary concerns?
								.icon.icon-plus
								.icon.icon-close
							.answer: p We'll be providing meals for most everyone at HackTJ, but if you have special concerns please <a href="mailto:hello@hacktj.org">let us know</a>.
				p.large If your question isn't answered here, just ask us: <a href="mailto:hello@hacktj.org">hello@hacktj.org</a>.
